{"id":682,"date":"2009-04-02T23:53:33","date_gmt":"2009-04-02T23:53:33","guid":{"rendered":""},"modified":"2015-03-24T03:58:29","modified_gmt":"2015-03-24T03:58:29","slug":"kde-4-2-2-is-out","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/news\/kde-4-2-2-is-out\/","title":{"rendered":"KDE 4.2.2 Is Out"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"http:\/\/www.kde.org\/announcements\/announce-4.2.2.php\">KDE 4.2.2 has been released<\/a> and is available for Kubuntu.<br \/>\n<!--break--><\/p>\n<h3>Jaunty (current development release)<\/h3>\n<p>Packages for Jaunty (current development release) are available.  If you use Jaunty you will be able to upgrade as normal.<\/p>\n<h3>8.10 (Intrepid)<\/h3>\n<p>Packages for Kubuntu 8.10 can be installed by following the instructions below.<\/p>\n<p><em>Note: These packages are not supported by Canonical; for a stable system it is not recommended to upgrade. KDE 4.2 will be officially supported as part of Kubuntu 9.04 being released April 23rd 2009.<\/em><\/p>\n<h4>Instructions<\/h4>\n<p>The updated packages for Kubuntu 8.10 are in the kubuntu-members-kde4 PPA. To update to KDE 4.2, please follow these instructions:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>\nRemove the koffice-data-kde4 package if you have it installed. The current koffice2 packages in the kubuntu-members-kde4 PPA are incompatible with the KDE 4.2 packages since they try to install icons to the same locations.<\/li>\n<li>\nFollow the <a href=\"https:\/\/help.ubuntu.com\/community\/Repositories\/Kubuntu\">Kubuntu Repository Guide<\/a> to enable <em>Recommended Updates<\/em> and <em>Unsupported Updates<\/em>.\n<\/li>\n<li>\nIn <em>Third Party Software<\/em> add:<br \/>\n<em>deb http:\/\/ppa.launchpad.net\/kubuntu-members-kde4\/ppa\/ubuntu intrepid main<\/em>\n<\/li>\n<li>\nOld Plasma packages are not compatible with KDE 4.2, you should uninstall any plasmoids.<\/li>\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">\nYou can now update any existing KDE 4 installation to 4.2 with Full Upgrade in the package manager, or using the Adept Updater tool in your system tray.\n<\/li>\n<li>\nNow log out. When you log in you will have KDE 4.2. Enjoy.\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h4>Notes<\/h4>\n<p>KDE 4.2.2 uses Akonadi which will install MySQL.  The MySQL packages in intrepid will ask for a password, you can set this to anything you like.<\/p>\n<p>Digikam will not install alongside these packages due to conflicting library versions.<\/p>\n<h3>Bugs<\/h3>\n<p>If you come across any issue which may be packaging related, it is recommended that you join the Kubuntu IRC channel (#kubuntu on irc.freenode.net) and query those in the channel for assistance.\n<\/p>\n<p>Thanks to Steve, Jonathan, Nathan, Roderick and awen for these packages.  <\/p>\n<p>If you want to see your name above, then join the Kubuntu Team.<br \/>\nMore information is available in the <a href=\"https:\/\/wiki.kubuntu.org\/Kubuntu\">Kubuntu Wiki<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>KDE 4.2.2 has been released and is available for Kubuntu. Jaunty (current development release) Packages for Jaunty (current development release) are available. If you use Jaunty you will be able to upgrade as normal. 8.10 (Intrepid) Packages for Kubuntu 8.10 can be installed by following the instructions below. Note: These&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[129],"tags":[142,145,178],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/682"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=682"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/kubuntu.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/post